Native persuasion support for a DS conversation with persuasion set to Vanilla.

1) COMPANION_PERSUASION_OPEN/_CLOSED around the native PersuasionDialog (a WindowModal shown by
   setVisible(true)), so the bottom-screen conversation overlay steps aside (anyServiceVanillaUp in
   EngineActivity) instead of covering the modal on the top screen, AND the controller-nav gate goes
   false so the controller reaches the modal. OPEN from PersuasionDialog::onOpen(); CLOSED from a new
   onClose() override (every close path — mouse Cancel / a persuade action / controller B — routes
   through setVisible(false) -> WindowBase::onClose). Once-guarded via gPersuasionCompanionOpen.

2) COMPANION_DIALOGUE_PERSUADE_AVAILABLE now carries the sPersuasion display string. When persuasion
   is Vanilla the DS overlay's "Persuade" entry routes back through the EXISTING topic bridge
   (CMPDLG:topic:<name> -> companionSelectEntry -> onSelectListItem(sPersuasion) ->
   mPersuasionDialog.setVisible(true)), opening the native modal — no new bridge needed. Previously
   the entry was gated to persuasion==DS only, so Vanilla persuasion had NO trigger in a DS
   conversation (and the modal never opened, so the step-aside never fired). The parser matches the
   token before the ':' so the availability flag still works; the name is unused when persuasion=DS.

dialogue.cpp is otherwise touched only by companion-dialogue-export.patch (applied earlier in the
chain); this patch applies after it. Kotlin: LogParser prefixes -> persuasionWindowOpen StateFlow +
dialoguePersuadeTopicName -> anyServiceVanillaUpFlow() (gated on game_ui_persuasion == VANILLA) and
the DS "Persuade" tap routing.
